        <para id="id64727">What is the voltage across the resistor in the circuit shown?


<figure id="id64742"><media id="id64742_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/PG10C9_021.png" id="id64742_onlineimage" width="135"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 135. --></image><image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/PG10C9_021.eps" id="id64742_printimage"/></media></figure>


 </para>
        </problem>
        <solution id="solfhsst_id626"> <list id="listfhsst_id626" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" class="stepwise">
        <item> <label> Check what you have and the units </label>
        <para id="id64769">We have a circuit with a battery and one resistor. We know the voltage across the battery. We want to find that voltage across the resistor.</para>
        <equation id="id64773">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              <m:mi mathvariant="normal">V</m:mi>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        </item> <item> <label> Applicable principles </label>
        <para id="id64817">We know that the voltage across the battery must be equal to the total voltage across all other circuit components.</para>
        <equation id="id64822">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>e</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:msub>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>o</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>l</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:msub>
            </m:mrow>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id64872">There is only one other circuit component, the resistor.</para>
        <equation id="id64878">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msub>
                <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mi>o</m:mi>
